 The headlight went out on my car, should I worry about replacing it soon?

The answer is yes. It’s not just a matter of convenience or safety for you and your passengers; it’s also the law in most states that all vehicles must have at least one working headlight. If you are caught driving with only one headlight, you could be fined up to $100. In addition, if your vehicle has more than two headlights (such as high-beams), then each light must work properly before being allowed onto public roads.

## What happens when a headlight goes out?

When a headlight goes out, it can cause problems for drivers who rely on them to see clearly at night. A broken bulb may not seem like much but there are many reasons why this might happen:

- The filament inside the bulb burns out due to overuse or age;
